{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01744SNkKCvndJfUeFTgjutr","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"es-cluster-0 is Running but not Ready. The readiness probe isn't passing. Let me check what's happening in the logs and potentially the issue.\n\nThe StatefulSet creates pods sequentially - it won't create es-cluster-1 until es-cluster-0 is Ready. But if es-cluster-0 needs es-cluster-1 and es-cluster-2 to form a quorum for the initial_master_nodes, there's a chicken-and-egg problem.\n\nWait, in ES 8.x, `cluster.initial_master_nodes` is just for bootstrapping the cluster. The first node to start (es-cluster-0) should be able to form the cluster on its own if it's listed in initial_master_nodes. \n\nThough ES typically requires a quorum of master-eligible nodes before marking itself as ready, so even with all three nodes in initial_master_nodes, the first node might be waiting for the others. Let me look at the logs to see what's actually blocking the readiness probe.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1750,"cache_read_input_tokens":43355,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1750},"output_tokens":23,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"dba7340a-94eb-4c5f-a0d8-815ed63dc982","uuid":"39dcbde5-d14f-4d7a-9cb8-2d304449d0da","request_id":"req_011CcfekYUD1zYRJCU1SZbUx"}
