{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01HcR84rsdaMRtHYcr9dP6SB","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The 3-node Elasticsearch 8.11.1 cluster is fully deployed and operational. Here's a summary of what was done:\n\n**Problem found:** The namespace had a running ES 7.17.9 cluster without TLS, wrong image, and missing secrets (`es-http-tls`, `elastic-password`).\n\n**Actions taken:**\n\n1. **Generated TLS certificates** — self-signed CA + server cert covering all pod DNS names (`es-cluster-{0,1,2}.es-cluster.elasticsearch.svc.cluster.local`), the `es-http` service, and `localhost`.\n\n2. **Created secrets** — `es-http-tls` (tls.crt, tls.key, ca.crt) and `elastic-password` (password=`elastic123`).\n\n3. **Deleted old resources** — removed the ES 7.17.9 StatefulSet and its PVCs (ES 8.x can't reuse 7.x data files).\n\n4. **Updated ConfigMap** — `es-config` now includes ES 8.x settings: `xpack.security.enabled`, `xpack.security.http.ssl.*`, `xpack.security.transport.ssl.*`, and full FQDN seed hosts.\n\n5. **Fixed seed_hosts** — changed from short-form (`es-cluster-0.es-cluster`) to full FQDN to ensure DNS resolution works reliably.\n\n6. **Deployed with `podManagementPolicy: Parallel`** — all 3 pods start simultaneously so they can form a quorum and elect a master.\n\n**Verified:**\n- Cluster status: **green**, 3 nodes, ES 8.11.1\n- HTTPS write: `test-index/_doc/1` created successfully\n- HTTPS read: document retrieved correctly\n- Service `es-http` routes to port 9200 inside the cluster"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":510,"cache_read_input_tokens":51477,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":510},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"dba7340a-94eb-4c5f-a0d8-815ed63